			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have spent a great amount of time in Droga solo. Truly solo. Not 2+ boxing as has been stated here. I find that oftentimes, mages lose out on soloing techniques when they 2+box. Case in point: a friend of mine who is also the same level but has leveled completely off 2 boxing with a druid has lost the "feel" for true soloing. He dies frequently when his druid fails an evac or misses a heal or whatever. He also makes up for this in obtaining xp for AA pretty fast. However, I want to speak regarding true soloing here in Droga.
<br />

<br />
I enter the nw side of Droga (main entrance). As soon as I enter, I call up my WoX pet (60 air) and buff and outfit him. Then I suspend pet (sp2) and invis. I then move down into Droga (drop down into the hidden pit area) and continue down past mobs until I get to the second open "clearing". If you hang a sharp left, there is a narrow hallway (safespot) you can use to setup. Get yourself ready to rumble. At the cul-de-sac, pull the left mob first and you will get him solo. Your buffed air pet (with DS) will take him down. Heal your pet when he's down to about 60~70% health with Planar renewal (1200 pt heal) This hallway has a little "hitched angle" to it that allows you to hide behind it to avoid getting hit with dispells and nukes. Keep your pet taunt ON.  The DS, pet taunt and stuns will keep the mobs attention as long as you are out of sight. Your pet heals with still go off while you are around the corner. Sit and med while pet tanks mobs safely. When mob is around 30%, Then I hit it with either the 900 pt rain or FBoT or SV. Usually depends on my mana. I am evoc spec'd and SCM3 so it's mana effecient for me to cast these at low mana costs. This will take him down to "run away" mode. But it is a slow walk and the pet's stuns will stop him most of the time. Also, it's a longer hallway out to where the next mob is so the safety margin is fairly wide. Med to fm because the next pull will net you two for sure and you CAN survive this with the AA pet mend and your heals. You will get two when you pull the rightmost mob. Just stay calm and just heal your pet. Trust me, I have done this many many times and it always works. When the mobs are down to less than 50%, you can rain them both providing you have the mana. I always do. I usually survive this twofer with about 40% mana left. Use your rods! Use your elemental draw. Use your pet form:water. Make sure you have KEI although I survive quite well without it. The last pull is the PH for the named and is single. Once you break this area, it's a snap to keep up with it. You can then pull outside the hallway to the open clearing area at will. It's constant and it's safe. Just watch out for higher level mobs wandering and the exp and loot will rock. You can try the nearby 3 named mobs as well for their loot drops. 
<br />

<br />
Just keep your head and don't panic and your survivability will increase dramatically. DPoC air pet is even better. I don't have RS as yet but I wouldn't use him down here as I have come to rely on WoX way too much and I trust what he can and cannot do in Droga. I have only died once due to a 3 mob pull and miscalculated my second suspended pet casting. Operator error <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Droga is fun and profitable for the soloer here once you know how to do it. The aggro range is not so huge here even for close proximity mobs so experiment. I have and it has yielded great results. Keep gate handy for you tremulous 2+boxers tho <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Cammyss
<br />
65 Epic Arch Convoker
<br />
The Fallen
<br />
Drinal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
